  "ocr_text": "COPY.
THE AMERICAN MINING CONGRESS,
Denver, Colorado, March 16, 1909.
Samuel Gompers,
President American Federation of Labor,
809 G St., N. W., Washington, D.C.
Sir:
Your kind favor of March 13th, suggesting the name of James O'Connell as a member of the Committee on the Standardization of Electrical Equipment, is at hand, and I thank you very much for your prompt attention to this matter.
As soon as the other members of this committee have been selected, I will notify Mr. O'Connell of his appointment, sending at the same time the names of the other members.
Thanking you for your attention to this matter, I am,
Very truly yours,
AMERICAN MINING CONGRESS
J. F. Calbreath, Secretary.
",
  "summary": "This letter, dated March 16, 1909, from the American Mining Congress in Denver, Colorado, addresses Samuel Gompers, President of the American Federation of Labor. It acknowledges Gompers' suggestion of James O'Connell for a committee on electrical equipment standardization. The secretary, J. F. Calbreath, thanks Gompers and promises to notify O'Connell of his appointment once the committee members are selected.",
